<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="433" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1814,2021]" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1814,1841]" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">Distribution.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nardo" authorityYear="1827" box="[491,597,1815,1841]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinodontidae" genus="Aphanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="433" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[491,597,1815,1841]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">Aphanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in coastal lagoons and estuaries of the Mediterranean Sea basin (
<figureCitation box="[227,296,1851,1877]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1525,1550]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,597,1497]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,597,1500]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Records of Aphanius species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3943899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3943899/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), where it is only absent from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[749,825,1852,1878]" name="France" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">France</collectingCountry>
(extirpated), 
<collectingCountry box="[978,1042,1851,1877]" name="Spain" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">Spain</collectingCountry>
(introduced) and 
<collectingCountry box="[1245,1346,1852,1878]" name="Morocco" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">Morocco</collectingCountry>
west of the Moulouya River estuary (
<bibRefCitation author="Valdesalici, S. &amp; Brahimi, A. &amp; Freyhof, J." box="[479,735,1887,1914]" pageId="12" pageNumber="433" pagination="541 - 550" refId="ref21490" refString="Valdesalici, S., Brahimi, A. &amp; Freyhof, J. (2019) First record of Aphanius almiriensis from Italy and notes on the distribution of Aphanius fasciatus (Teleostei: Aphaniidae). Journal of Applied Ichthyology, 35, 541 - 550. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jai. 13873" type="journal article" year="2019">
Valdesalici 
<emphasis box="[611,660,1887,1913]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="434" pageId="12" pageNumber="433" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1814,2021]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1436,153,215]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="434" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1923,1949]" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kottelat, Barbieri &amp; Stoumboudi" authorityYear="2007" box="[324,562,1923,1949]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinodontidae" genus="Aphanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="433" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="almiriensis">
<emphasis box="[324,562,1923,1949]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">Aphanius almiriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[620,753,1923,1949]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinodontidae" genus="Aphanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="433" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis box="[620,753,1923,1949]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">A. fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are superficially very similar and difficult to identify in the field. Kottelat 
<emphasis box="[313,369,1959,1985]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">et al.</emphasis>
(2007) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Valdesalici, S. &amp; Brahimi, A. &amp; Freyhof, J." box="[502,768,1959,1985]" pageId="12" pageNumber="433" pagination="541 - 550" refId="ref21490" refString="Valdesalici, S., Brahimi, A. &amp; Freyhof, J. (2019) First record of Aphanius almiriensis from Italy and notes on the distribution of Aphanius fasciatus (Teleostei: Aphaniidae). Journal of Applied Ichthyology, 35, 541 - 550. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jai. 13873" type="journal article" year="2019">
Valdesalici 
<emphasis box="[632,687,1959,1985]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
discussed the characters distinguishing these two species in detail. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cavraro, F. &amp; Malavasi, S. &amp; Torricelli, P. &amp; Gkenas, C. &amp; Liousia, V. &amp; Leonardos, I. &amp; Kappas, I. &amp; Abatzopoulos, T. J. &amp; Triantafyllidis, A." box="[228,466,1995,2021]" pageId="12" pageNumber="433" pagination="153 - 166" refId="ref17977" refString="Cavraro, F., Malavasi, S., Torricelli, P., Gkenas, C., Liousia, V., Leonardos, I., Kappas, I., Abatzopoulos, T. J. &amp; Triantafyllidis, A. (2017) Genetic structure of the South European toothcarp Aphanius fasciatus (Actinopterygii: Cyprinodontidae) populations in the Mediterranean basin with a focus on the Venice lagoon, The European Zoological Journal, 84 (1), 153 - 166. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 24750263.2017.1290154" type="journal article" year="2017">
Cavraro 
<emphasis box="[326,384,1995,2021]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="433">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
documented the existence of intraspecific genetic diversity between different popula- tions of 
<taxonomicName box="[247,380,153,179]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinodontidae" genus="Aphanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="434" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis box="[247,380,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="434">A. fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These differences are clearly intraspecific and specimens we examined could not be distin- guished morphologically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
